training at a suburban baghdad soccer ground 
after iraqs millionmember regular army these men and women 
are saddam husseins second line of defense in the confrontation 
with the usdominated multinational force 
every day the iraqi authorities organize marches through 
baghdad and other cities by popular army recruits among them 
elderly grayhaired men and guntoting women some with heads 
covered by scarves in the islamic tradition 
teenage boys clutch rocketpropelled grenade launchers and 
chant down down bush 
iraqi officials boast that 8 million men and women have 
volunteered for the popular army in a wave of patriotic fervor 
