<TEXT>
the deadline for filing claims under the 
national vaccine injury compensation program has been extended 
federal officials said tuesday 
congress moved the deadline to jan 31 for claimants injured on 
or before oct 1 1988 the earlier deadline had been oct 1 1990 
those who miss the deadline may pursue their claims in civil 
court but the federal program was set up as a faster less 
expensive procedure 
the program pays compensation for vaccinerelated injuries 
requiring petitioners to prove only that the injury is related to a 
vaccine not that the manufacturer of the vaccine was at fault 
it covers the diphtheria tetanus and pertussis vaccine the 
measles mumps and rubella vaccine the oral polio vaccine and the 
inactivated polio vaccine said the department of health and human 
services 
claims for injuries that occurred after oct 1 1988 must be 
filed by deadlines stipulated in the national childhood injury act 
the amount of compensation is determined by a us claims court 
based on the needs of the injured person and the extent of the 
injury the maximum death benefit is 250000 
information about how to file a petition may be obtained from 
the us claims court 717 madison place nw washington dc 
