basic problems faced by us thrifts the upanddown cycle of the 
housing market 
currently us institutions are suffering from declining home 
sales but in the soviet union demand for housing long 
unsatisfied by the communist economy is strong 
if the environment is stable the demand for housing is 
virtually unlimited sorokin said thats where the savings and 
loan system of the soviet union will be cashing in 
