foreign publishers must obtain the singapore 
governments permission to sell their newspapers and magazines here 
effective dec 1 the communication and information ministry said 
tuesday 
under an amendment to the newspaper and printing presses act 
the communications and information minister also may exempt 
publications from having to apply for a permit the ministry said 
in a statement 
it said communications and information minister yeo ning hong 
will exempt 14 foreign publications which do not report regularly 
on singapore and have not interfered in singapores domestic 
affairs 
the act is not intended to curb the circulation of foreign 
publications or the free flow of information the statement said 
it is meant to overcome problems encountered with a small 
number of offshore publications which report on singapore 
regularly 
some of these publications had built up sizeable circulations 
in singapore and attempted to play the same role in singapore 
politics as they did in their own countries taking sides and 
