kyowa bank ltd and saitama bank ltd announced 
tuesday they have agreed to merge effective next april 1 creating 
what would be japans eighth largest bank with 178 billion in 
deposits 
the new bank will have 459 branches including 16 overseas and 
a work force of 15502 the two banking companies said in a 
statement 
we consider our mission to be to become the most excellent 
bank respected by society in the retail field taking 
advantage of mutual tradition and merits takeo masuno president 
of saitama bank said at a news conference 
kosuke yokote president of kyowa bank joined him at the news 
conference to announce the merger which is subject to approval by 
the finance ministry the fair trade commission and japans central 
bank 
a statement by saitama bank said the merger would help 
strengthen management to cope with liberalization and 
internationalization of japans financial markets 
the deal would be the second involving major japanese banks in 
the past year 
in april mitsui bank and taiyo kobe bank merged becoming 
japans secondlargest bank in terms of deposits with 43539 
billion yen or 335 billion 
the largest bank in japan is daiichi kangyo bank with deposits 
of 46946 billion yen or 361 billion 
yasushi mieno a bank of japan governor said he expects the 
merger of kyowa bank and saitama bank to contribute to the strength 
of the japanese banking industry 
in a news release mieno called the merger significant because 
the merger appears to have been spurred by deregulation of the 
japanese banking industry and increased competition from abroad 
mieno said the merger appears to be aimed at enabling the banks 
management to respond more fully to the diverse needs of their 
customers and to make the most of their strength in retail banking 
the new merged bank would have combined deposits of 23179 
billion yen or about 178 billion 
as of may 15 kyowa japans 10th biggest bank in terms of 
deposits had 239 branches and employed 7971 people with deposits 
totaling 11902 billion yen or about 92 billion it said 
as of july 1 saitama was japans 11th biggest bank with 212 
branches and 7531 employees and deposits totaling 11277 billion 
