<TEXT>
interest rates on shortterm treasury 
securities fell in tuesdays auction to their lowest level in more 
than two years 
the treasury department sold 10 billion in threemonth bills at 
an average discount rate of 705 percent down from 707 percent 
last week another 10 billion was sold in sixmonth bills at an 
average discount rate of 702 percent down from 705 percent last 
week 
the rates were the lowest since threemonth bills sold for 694 
percent on aug 8 1988 and sixmonth bills averaged 699 percent 
on july 11 1988 
the new discount rates understate the actual return to investors 
728 percent for threemonth bills with a 10000 bill selling 
for 982180 and 738 percent for a sixmonth bill selling for 
964510 
in a separate report the federal reserve said the average yield 
for oneyear treasury bills the most popular index for making 
changes in adjustable rate mortgages fell to 735 percent last 
week down from 741 percent the previous week 
