<TEXT>
the european court of justice tuesday approved 
the european communitys 1985 ban on the use of hormones in cattle 
breeding 
the court ruled tuesday that the ban was justified to allay 
health concerns of european consumers as expressed by the european 
parliament the european economic and social committee and various 
european consumers associations 
the luxembourg court at first voided the european directive 
mainly for legal technicalities and the ec immediately revised its 
text to comply with the court objections 
european producers of pharmaceutical and veterinary products 
then attacked the ban before the court claiming there was no 
scientific evidence the use of hormones was harmful to humans 
the 1985 ban led to us trade reprisals the us government 
claimed its cattle breeders were losing 100 million worth of 
exports because of the ban and slapped tariffs on various european 
food exports 
</TEXT>
